    {
      "id": "8e64e340e8143c19626132924f7efd12eda44131",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-27 23:57:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nTo be honest, I'd prefer that this be capped at 32TB, which is a reasonable upper bound for 4TB drives in a RAID-6 8+2 system.  There are just too many potential problems with RHEL5 kernels that I don't think it is wise to allow new large systems to be installed with larger LUNs in the future.\n\nIf users have storage systems over 32TB at some point in the future they should really be using Lustre 2.1 or 2.4.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
